Full Description: Techistential is the global Foresight Strategy & Futures Intelligence practice based in San Francisco.  Our Group also includes the Disruptive Futures Institute, a Think Tank offering executive education, research and thought leadership on adapting to our increasingly complex and unpredictable world. The Disruptive Futures Institute LLC is the publisher of the bestselling seminal four-volume collection: The Definitive Guide to Thriving on Disruption (www.thrivingondisruption.com). Founded by bestselling foresight strategist Roger Spitz, Techistential’s renowned Board, Anticipatory Governance & Investor foresight practice works with leaders and their organizations globally to capitalize on disruption as a springboard to drive sustainable value creation. We help clients anticipate next order impacts of accelerating change and reinvent governance systems for the disruptive 21st century. Techistential's dedicated Sustainable Futures Practice provides climate foresight-driven advice on the global energy transition, which is creating paradigm shifts in value and business models. Techistential advises organizations, companies and entrepreneurs worldwide, as well as their governance bodies and investors on: - Strategic Foresight - Sustainable Value Creation & Climate Foresight - Anticipatory Governance: Board & Investor Foresight Practice - Technology Foresight, Design Fiction & Innovation - Artificial Intelligence, Ethical & Existential Foresight - Techistential Center for Human & Artificial Intelligence - DFI Sustainability & Climate Academy From his research and publications, Roger Spitz coined the term Techistentialism which studies the nature of human beings, existence, and decision-making in our technological world. Today, we face both technological and existential conditions that can no longer be separated. Roger Spitz chairs Techistential's Center for Human & Artificial Intelligence.  Roger Spitz has written four influential books as part of “The Definitive Guide to Thriving on Disruption” collection, which became an instant classic. He publishes extensively on decision-making in uncertain and complex environments, with bestselling books in Business Technology Innovation, Future Studies, Green Business, Sustainable Economic Development, Business Education, Strategic Management & Forecasting. For Interviews, Media & Speaking requests: - Contact: media@techistential.ai For futures projects and inquiries on our strategic foresight practices: - Contact: info@techistential.ai - https://www.techistential.ai - Instagram & Twitter: @techistential - LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/company/techistential

Description: Crowd Purchasing Platform | Electronics Producer | FLIR Premium Partner |
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: Welcome to group getting! In 2013, we tried to buy special purpose processors for a passion project. They were only sold in lots of 1000. After scouring the internet for a solution, we discovered that there was no secure platform for collectively purchasing existing products with minimum order restrictions. Getting a group together for a bulk purchase was a difficult and risky proposition, and crowdfunding platforms were no help. Traditional crowdfunding sites are great. But, they neglect independent buyers who need to team up with other buyers around the world to get bulk pricing discounts and access components, end user products, and services that have high minimum order quantities. So, we set out to fill this gap. We created GroupGets to provide an intuitive group buying platform where professionals and enthusiasts can participate in collective purchasing as easily as they buy anything else online, and get rewarded for creating group buys and helping others get around minimum order requirements. No Vaporware. No year-long shipping delays. Just simple, secure group buying. GroupGets is where the rest of us—the makers, hobbyists, DIY engineers, crafters, artists, small businesses, and deal seekers—get together and hack minimum order restrictions.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Financial Services, Hardware
Founders: Kurt Kiefer, Ronald Justin, Sashi Ono
